  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
      <h5 class="text-center murdoc-red">Installation Guide</h5>
      <p>First, check if you already have Ruby installed by running "ruby -v" in your terminal.</p>
      <h6>Install by operating system package manager:</h6>
      <%# <pre> %>
        <div class="row">

          <div class="col-sm-4 instruction-card">
            <em>Ubuntu or Debian</em>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
            <i class="devicon-ubuntu-plain colored mx-2"></i><i class="devicon-debian-plain colored mx-2"></i>
            </div>
            <kbd>sudo apt-get install ruby-full</kbd>
          </div>

          <div class="col-sm-4 instruction-card">
            <em>macOS</em>
            <i class="fa-brands fa-apple"></i>
            <kbd>brew install ruby</kbd>
          </div>

          <div class="col-sm-4 instruction-card">
            <em>Arch Linux</em>
            <%= image_tag "archlinux.png" %>
            <kbd>sudo pacman -S ruby</kbd>
          </div>

          <div class="col-sm-4 instruction-card">
            <em>Gentoo</em>
            <i class="devicon-gentoo-plain colored"></i>
            <kbd>sudo emerge dev-lang/ruby</kbd>
          </div>

          <div class="col-sm-4 instruction-card">
            <em>CentOS or Red</em>
            <i class="fa-brands fa-centos"></i>
            <kbd>sudo emerge dev-lang/ruby</kbd>
          </div>

        </div>
        <%# <code>

            <i class="devicon-ubuntu-plain colored"></i> <em>For Ubuntu or Debian</em>
            $ <code><kbd>sudo apt-get install ruby-full</kbd></code>

          $ sudo dnf install ruby

          # macOS
          $ brew install ruby

          # Windows
          $ choco install ruby

          # Arch Linux
          $ sudo pacman -S ruby
        </code> %>
      <%# </pre> %>
      <p>Once the installation is complete, set the global Ruby version to be used by default with the command "rbenv global 3.1.2".</p>
      <p>Verify that the correct version of Ruby is being used by running "ruby -v" in your terminal.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
      <h3 class="text-center">Ruby on Rails Installation</h3>
      <p>Install the Node.js runtime environment, which is required by some Ruby on Rails features. You can download it from the official website (https://nodejs.org/en/download/) or use a package manager.</p>
      <p>Install the Yarn package manager, which is also required by some Ruby on Rails features. You can download it from the official website (https://classic.yarnpkg.com/en/docs/install/) or use a package manager.</p>
      <p>Install the latest version of Ruby on Rails using the command "gem install rails".</p>
      <p>Verify that Ruby on Rails is installed correctly by running "rails -v" in your terminal.</p>
      <p>Congratulations, you have successfully installed Ruby and Ruby on Rails! You are now ready to start building your web applications.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
